      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i'm trying to get a better sense of the logic used there. for Case B, you mentioned being \"more cautious about leniency\" because of the employment history. do you think that kind of instability is usually seen as a higher risk for re-offending compared to someone from a stable background? like, would a judge generally assume someone from an urban environment with a spotty work history is more likely to go back to crime?",
